[7] Brazil
Date: Thu 5 Sep 2019
Source: Rio Times [abridged, edited]
https://riotimesonline.com/brazil-news/brazil/life-brazil/health-ministry-confirms-2753-cases-of-measles-in-brazil-98-in-sao-paulo/


The Health Ministry reported yesterday [Wed 4 Sep 2019], that from [9 Jun to 31 Aug 2019], 2753 cases of measles were confirmed in Brazil. In that period, there were 4 deaths due to the complication of the patients' health condition, 3 in Sao Paulo and 1 in Pernambuco. According to Health Surveillance Secretary Wanderson Oliveira, 3 of the deaths were babies under the age of 1.

Compared to the information released on [Wed 28 Aug 2019], there was an increase of 18% in the number of people infected.

